text: Dover is a city in Strafford County, New Hampshire, United States. The population was 32,741 at the 2020 census, the largest in the New Hampshire Seacoast region. It is the county seat of Strafford County, and home to Wentworth-Douglass Hospital, the Woodman Institute Museum, and the Children's Museum of New Hampshire. ==References== Category:Cities in New Hampshire Category:County seats in New Hampshire
title: Dover, New Hampshire
